The paper proposes a method for click-through rate prediction, which is a common problem in online advertising and recommender systems. The method involves automatically learning high-order feature interactions of input features, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of feature engineering. The proposed method uses a self-attentive neural network, which is a popular technique in natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
